## 6. Provenance

```
rpe.service_evidence.captured   — on admissible evidence capture (atomic with the evidence write)
  payload: account_id, property_id, lease_id, obligation_instance_id,
           official_info_sheet_identity, service_evidence_timestamp, evidence_type,
           captured_by, capture_source, demo_mode
rpe.obligation.discharged       — on the open → discharged transition (atomic with the posture change)
  payload: obligation_instance_id, evaluation_id, evidence_id(s),
           official_info_sheet_identity, service_evidence_timestamp,
           previous_posture=open, new_posture=discharged, reason, demo_mode
rpe.obligation.discharged_basis_changed_flag  — when a discharged obligation gets a later
           not_affected/needs_data (review flag, NOT a posture move)
```
The discharge event records *which evidence* discharged it — so the eventual Proof Pack can show "discharged, because this official artefact was served on this date, proven by this evidence." Same atomic + demo_mode discipline as all prior events.

