## 7. Tests

```
Admissibility (§2):
  - discharge with official_info_sheet_identity only (no service proof) → REJECTED, posture stays open
  - discharge with service timestamp only (no artefact identity) → REJECTED, posture stays open
  - discharge with an inadmissible artefact source (filename/tag/free text) → REJECTED
  - discharge with BOTH admissible → succeeds (see below)
Discharge (the door):
  - open obligation + admissible evidence (both fields) → posture open → discharged via engine;
    rpe.service_evidence.captured + rpe.obligation.discharged events present, atomic
  - evidence capture does NOT directly set discharged (posture moves only via reconciliation RPC)
Transition guards:
  - attempt discharge on a superseded obligation → REJECTED (non-open)
  - attempt discharge on a requires_review obligation → REJECTED (non-open)
★ Freeze rule (§5 — load-bearing):
  - discharged obligation + later not_affected eval → posture STAYS discharged;
    discharged-basis-changed flag raised; NO auto-supersession, NO posture event moving it off discharged
  - discharged obligation + later needs_data eval → stays discharged, flag raised
  - discharged obligation + later affected eval → idempotent, no change
  - flag visibility (amend 2): a raised discharged-basis-changed flag is observable in the
    diagnostic/read model (readiness or posture summary), not just buried in a column
Evidence record (amend 1):
  - service evidence is a first-class queryable record (own table/row), linked to obligation_instance,
    with all minimum fields — NOT only JSON on obligation_instance
  - the discharge can be traced by query: obligation → evidence → official artefact + timestamp + captured_by
Boundary (still holds from VS-2B):
  - renters_rights_tasks.sent = true on a discharged or open obligation → NO posture move
  - direct UPDATE to discharged outside reconciliation RPC → blocked (RLS + constraint trigger)
Hard checks:
  - demo_mode = true on every evidence record, discharge, and event (Gate-B leak → STOP)
  - account-scoped: ownerB cannot capture evidence / discharge ownerA's obligation (behavioral, not structural)
  - ★ cross-account READS reject by THROWING (system-wide rule): every VS-2C read RPC — evidence
    reads, list/summary of evidence or discharged obligations, any readiness/posture surface that now
    includes discharge state — THROWS an authorization error when accessed cross-account. NOT a neutral
    empty/not_run payload. This matches the write RPCs and the get_rra_capture_readiness fix: ALL
    account-scoped RPE RPCs reject cross-account, no mixed read/write model. Behavioral test, not string-match.
```

