## 10. After VS-2C

The obligation lifecycle is now complete for the demo-mode slice: `affected → open` (VS-2B), `open → discharged` on admissible evidence (VS-2C), with `superseded`/`requires_review` for changed bases and discharged frozen against silent erasure. Every transition is provenanced and demo-only. The engine can now show not just "this tenancy is affected" but "this obligation was discharged, because this official artefact was served on this date, proven by this evidence" — which is the Proof Pack's eventual content. **VS-2D** then resolves the one deferred question (how a discharged obligation reconciles when its basis later changes — candidate C), over a lifecycle that's otherwise complete and proven. Gate-B sign-off remains the gate before any of this becomes customer-facing.

